<subSubSection id="61ADDBE97442BF50CBF3FADBFA99F871" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" type="description">
<paragraph id="290888627442BF56CBF3FADBFCAFF969" blockId="10.[151,1437,1570,2027]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56CBF3FADBFE2FF905" bold="true" box="[199,414,1678,1703]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Description. Body</emphasis>
length: 
<quantity id="EE4F25877442BF56CACFFADBFD8FF904" box="[507,574,1678,1703]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
, Head width: 
<quantity id="EE4F25877442BF56C9EFFADAFCAEF904" box="[731,799,1679,1703]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
, thorax width: 
<quantity id="EE4F25877442BF56C8FDFADAFB93F904" box="[969,1058,1679,1703]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
; abdomen width 
<quantity id="EE4F25877442BF56CFD7FADAFA8BF904" box="[1251,1338,1679,1703]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
tapering to 
<quantity id="EE4F25877442BF56CB80FAE7FEB8F968" box="[180,265,1714,1739]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
on anal segment. Coloration: yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="290888627442BF57CBF3FA83FDEFFEBF" blockId="10.[151,1437,1570,2027]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="66" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">
Head (ventral): anterior and posterior antennal processes (
<figureCitation id="B18C94E77442BF56C856FA83FC02F94D" box="[866,947,1750,1775]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1955,1977]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,337,1934]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Pupa of Phthiria fulva Meigen: a. lateral view; b. dorsal view; c. two last segments (lateral view); d. head (lateral view); e. last segments (dorsal view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/837151/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Figs. 6</figureCitation>
a, d) united as a pyramid-shaped truncated tubercle, margins well sclerotized, blackish brown, apex heavily sclerotized, black, with two very short denticles; median facial spines substitute by two hairs; lateral facial spines as two small swellings; proboscis and maxillary sheaths smooth; anterior and posterior coxal sheaths smooth; proboscis sheath extending to about same length as leg sheaths. Wing sheath and thoracic area smooth (
<figureCitation id="B18C94E77442BF56C9DBFB33FC84F8DD" box="[751,821,1894,1919]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1955,1977]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,337,1934]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Pupa of Phthiria fulva Meigen: a. lateral view; b. dorsal view; c. two last segments (lateral view); d. head (lateral view); e. last segments (dorsal view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/837151/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
b). Abdominal tergite I (
<figureCitation id="B18C94E77442BF56CF7BFB33FB25F8DD" box="[1103,1172,1894,1919]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1955,1977]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,337,1934]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Pupa of Phthiria fulva Meigen: a. lateral view; b. dorsal view; c. two last segments (lateral view); d. head (lateral view); e. last segments (dorsal view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/837151/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
b) without spines, only with row of six long, yellowish setae on anterior margin; segments II to VII laterally with one pair of long setae, medially with a transverse row of black spines intercalated with long setae, each row with seven backwardly curved spines inserted in sclerotized plates; lateral spines smaller than median ones; tergite VIII (
<figureCitation id="B18C94E77442BF56CFD4FB87FA92F849" box="[1248,1315,2002,2027]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1955,1977]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,337,1934]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Pupa of Phthiria fulva Meigen: a. lateral view; b. dorsal view; c. two last segments (lateral view); d. head (lateral view); e. last segments (dorsal view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/837151/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
e) laterally with three pairs of yellowish setae, dorsally with a row of four backwardly curved spines intercalated with long setae, without sclerotized plate at base of spines; tergite IX (
<figureCitation id="B18C94E77443BF57C851FCE9FC1CFF77" box="[869,941,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1955,1977]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,337,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,337,1934]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Pupa of Phthiria fulva Meigen: a. lateral view; b. dorsal view; c. two last segments (lateral view); d. head (lateral view); e. last segments (dorsal view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/837151/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
c, 7c) with two pairs of processes, ventral posterolateral processes long, about 2.0 times longer than dorsal ones, curved, brownish, apically darkened; dorsal processes short, straight, darker apically.
</paragraph>
<caption id="7DC8D8EA7443BF57CBA3FBF6FDA0F87A" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/837151/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" targetBox="[151,1436,337,1934]" targetPageId="11">
<paragraph id="290888627443BF57CBA3FBF6FDA0F87A" blockId="11.[151,1436,1955,2008]" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="1BC354707443BF57CBA3FBF6FEBAF81B" bold="true" box="[151,267,1955,1977]" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">FIGURE 6</emphasis>
. Pupa of 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17443BF57CA5AFBF6FDE2F81B" authority="Meigen" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1804" box="[366,595,1955,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis id="1BC354707443BF57CA5AFBF6FE73F81B" box="[366,450,1955,1977]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">Phthiria</emphasis>
<emphasis id="1BC354707443BF57CAFDFBF6FE4DF81B" box="[457,508,1955,1977]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">fulva</emphasis>
Meigen
</taxonomicName>
