</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 8b, c), showed that 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17445BF51CF62FD51FAD9FEBF" authority="Fabricius" authorityName="Fabricius" box="[1110,1384,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis id="1BC354707445BF51CF62FD51FB47FEBE" box="[1110,1270,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="68">Phthiria fulva</emphasis>
Fabricius
</taxonomicName>
is a useful parasitoid in the north of 
<collectingCountry id="51A0C8F27445BF51C924FD7DFDF1FE9D" box="[528,576,296,319]" name="Iran" pageId="13" pageNumber="68">Iran</collectingCountry>
, on 
<location id="2C68DEB97445BF51C940FD72FCE2FE9D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:A11E39747442BF52CBA3F9EDFC2BFE72:2C68DEB97445BF51C940FD72FCE2FE9D" box="[628,851,295,320]" country="Iran" name="Hosseinabad Forest" pageId="13" pageNumber="68">Hosseinabad Forest</location>
(Fig. 8a). This finding broadens the host range of 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17445BF51CBA3FD19FF44FEC6" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1820" box="[151,245,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1BC354707445BF51CBA3FD19FF44FEC6" box="[151,245,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="68">Phthiria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to include family 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17445BF51CAF5FD19FDC5FEC7" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1829" box="[449,628,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Yponomeutidae</taxonomicName>
, whose members are commonly known as fruit moths.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="290888627445BF51CBA3FB1AFE13F826" blockId="13.[151,1436,1871,1924]" pageId="13" pageNumber="68">
